@NODE "Mail_28" " DICE strins() (was: Digest Number 6) "
From: Stephen Williams <sw@nysa.u-net.com>
Date: 04-26-99 22:14:14
Subject: @{b}DICE strins() (was: Digest Number 6)@{ub}

From: Stephen Williams <sw@nysa.u-net.com>

Stephan Lichtendahl <s.e.m.lichtendahl@its.tudelft.nl> wrote:
> Actually, the string.h in DICE does contain a insert string into string
> function, although it isn't an ANSI function...

If anyone decides to use this function, don't forget that it assumes
that the source string has room to fit the destination string, eg

{
  char foo[10] = "Hello ";
  strins((char *)((int)foo + 6), "World!");
}

won't work, as "Hello World!" is 13 characters including the final
null, but storage for only ten chars was allocated.

-Stephen



