> From: Bob Lanham <BobL@leading.net>

> Can anybody show me the correct way to construct a file path?  Below is
> the way I've done it, but this way does not work at the root
> directories. For example it can't load the file Ram:myfile.iff.

Have a look at AddPart() (dos.library):

success = AddPart(pathname, filename, size)

filename will be added to pathname and size gives the size of buffer,
pathname points to.

Ciao, Alfred


