@NODE "Mail_90" " Opening A Library "
From: Mike Carter <mike.carter@bigfoot.com>
Date: 04-26-99 02:41:14
Subject: @{b}Opening A Library@{ub}

Somebody asked on the list how to go about using specific functions in
C of Amiga.  Well using run-time libraries you have access to many
functions.  Best to get the developer docs fore the specific library -
usually the files known as AutoDocs.

To use a runtime library (as found in your LIBS: directory) you need
to open them within your program.  Attached is an offical demo source
example from the ROM kernal manuals.

Dinky do,


Mike.


