@NODE "Mail_104" " Re: Programs Stack "
From: Martin Harris <harrism@ihug.co.nz>
Date: 04-29-99 02:06:37
Subject: @{b}Re: Programs Stack@{ub}

From: Martin Harris <harrism@ihug.co.nz>

Greetings and Salutations, Mike.

On 29-Apr-99, [1mMike[0m was saying...

> I'd like to launch a program with a specififc stack value.  How is it
> done?  Currently I'm generating a small AmigaDOS script in T: and then
> executing it from within my C code but that's messy and slooow.

These three Dos functions you can check out for launching new processes.
Execute(), CreateNewProc() and SystemTagList(). Though just checking, with
Execute() you don't seem to be able to change the stack value. But with the
other two, they both recognise the tag NP_StackValue. 

Yours, etc etc.
