I don't know the exact syntax of the amos basic commands but if you insert
this at the top of your source file...

#include <exec/types.h>
#define peek(a) [1m((UBYTE [0m)a)
#define leek(a) [1m((UWORD [0m)a)
#define deek(a) [1m((ULONG [0m)a)
#define poke(a, b) [1m((UBYTE [0m)a)=b
#define loke(a, b) [1m((UWORD [0m)a)=b
#define doke(a, b) [1m((ULONG [0m)a)=b

...I guess that you got what you want (assuming that 'l' stands for word and
'd' stands for long word).

/Jonas

